RNA-seq Workflow (HackBio NGS Internship 2025)
This workflow summarizes the main steps used for QC, trimming, alignment, quantification, and downstream analysis of RNA-seq data in the Bipolar II microglia transcriptomics project.

1. Project Setup
mkdir project2
cd project2
mkdir raw_data qc_results multiqc trim alignment_star alignment_logs counts ref scripts

2. Data Download

Download FASTQ files from SRA.
Script stored as:

scripts/download_data.sh

3. Quality Control
fastqc raw_data/* -o qc_results/
multiqc qc_results/ -o multiqc/

4. Trimming

Run trimming script:

bash scripts/trimming.sh


Outputs:

trim/trimmed/

trim/fastp_reports/

5. Mapping with STAR

Build genome index:

mkdir -p ref/star_index

STAR \
  --runThreadN 8 \
  --runMode genomeGenerate \
  --genomeDir ref/star_index \
  --genomeFastaFiles ref/Homo_sapiens_assembly38.fasta


Align reads:

bash scripts/mapping.sh

6. Gene Counting
featureCounts -T 8 -p \
  -a counts/gencode.v38.annotation.gtf \
  -o counts/gene_counts.txt \
  alignment_star/*.bam

7. Differential Expression (R / DESeq2)

Performed using DESeq2 to identify differentially expressed genes.

8. Functional Enrichment

Performed using ShinyGO to identify enriched pathways and biological processes.
